title: For Sale:  FN Mauser .30-06 JC Higgins Model 50
postcontent:
History:The model 50 was produced by belgium's Fabrique Nationale using a commercial 98 mauser action and a 22 inch chrome lined barrel from High Standard. The rifles were only chambered in .270 Win and .30-06 Springfield. Mine is chambered in .30-06. FN Belgium made actions of the the HIGHEST quality and durability, though it is obvious this rifle was rarely ever used. It is said that if a gun like this was built today, using this FN action, the price would easily exceed $1,500. Please do your research on this FINE firearm, collectors everywhere are seeking this model. I am afraid to sell such a rare firearm, I'm sure I will regret it soon. Condition:It is obvious this rifle has seen very little use. The walnut stock is in perfect condition, and the 'tiger stripe' grain is spectaular. Sling swivels and checkering were never added and I am quite glad. The original scope is mounted on the rifle and works great. The gun is COMPLETELY original from around 1950:  
-2.5X JC Higgins brand scope (original)
